title: The road is very, very primitive in sections.
Ed's tent on the island campsite.
A Mount Rainier pin to add to the collection.
The raging, glacially fed Carbon River.
Evidence of flooding on the Carbon River.
Looking up the Carbon valley. Carbon Glacier in the distance.
Making eggs with the Trangia backpacker set
Making coffee with the Esbit coffee maker.
A better section of Carbon River Road.
The edge of Carbon Glacier, lowest glacier in the continental United States.
My tent on the island campsite. The water was a moat protecting us from the yahoo campers around us.
The log that served as footbridge to our island campsite.
Ed pushes on through the boulder field.
Sunset over Ipsut Creek Campground, Saturday.
Ed worn out by the boulders on the road.
